  "ai_usage": "Use for premium/creative sites to add tactile momentum. Each frame, compute velocity = scrollY − lastScrollY, smooth it toward 0 with a decay (lerp), clamp to ±--max-skew, and write transform: skewY(v) (optionally scaleY). Apply to a wrapper, not body. Clamp so text stays legible and disable under prefers-reduced-motion. Use one rAF loop, not a scroll listener per event.",
  "path": "effects/scroll-effects/scroll-velocity-skew.html",
  "source": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n  <title>Scroll Velocity Skew</title>\n  <script type=\"application/json\" id=\"effect-meta\">\n  {\n    \"id\": \"scroll-velocity-skew\",\n    \"title\": \"Scroll Velocity Skew\",\n    \"summary\": \"Content skews and squashes in proportion to scroll speed, then springs back to rest — a fluid, physical scroll feel.\",\n    \"description\": \"Tracks scroll velocity each frame and maps it to a skewY (and slight scale) on the content, which eases back to zero when you stop. Fast flicks bend the page; slow scrolls barely move. A signature 'smooth scroll' flourish on award-style sites.\",\n    \"theme\": \"scroll-effects\",\n    \"categories\": [\"scroll\", \"animation\", \"javascript\"],\n    \"tags\": [\"scroll-velocity\", \"skew\", \"momentum\", \"physical\", \"smooth-scroll\", \"2026-trend\"],\n    \"tech\": [\"css\", \"js\"],\n    \"era\": \"2020s\",\n    \"difficulty\": \"intermediate\",\n    \"dependencies\": [],\n    \"browser_support\": \"All modern browsers.\",\n    \"performance_notes\": \"A single requestAnimationFrame loop computing velocity and writing one transform. transform-only — GPU-friendly. Loop is cheap and self-limiting.\",\n    \"accessibility_notes\": \"Purely decorative motion; content remains fully readable and in order. Disabled entirely under prefers-reduced-motion. Clamp max skew so text never becomes unreadable.\",\n    \"customization\": [\n      { \"name\": \"--max-skew\", \"description\": \"Skew clamp (deg)\", \"default\": \"8\" },\n      { \"name\": \"ease factor\", \"description\": \"How fast it springs back (lerp)\", \"default\": \"0.85 decay\" }\n    ],\n    \"variations\": [\"Skew only images, not text\", \"Map velocity to letter-spacing instead\", \"Horizontal skewX for sideways scrollers\"],\n    \"related\": [\"parallax-layers\",\"sticky-stack-cards\"],\n    \"ai_usage\": \"Use for premium/creative sites to add tactile momentum. Each frame, compute velocity = scrollY − lastScrollY, smooth it toward 0 with a decay (lerp), clamp to ±--max-skew, and write transform: skewY(v) (optionally scaleY). Apply to a wrapper, not body. Clamp so text stays legible and disable under prefers-reduced-motion. Use one rAF loop, not a scroll listener per event.\"\n  }\n  </script>\n  <style>\n    :root{--max-skew:8;}\n    *{box-sizing:border-box}body{margin:0;background:#0b0d12;color:#e8ecf6;font-family:system-ui,sans-serif}\n    .skewer{transform-origin:center top;will-change:transform}\n    .hero{min-height:60vh;display:grid;place-items:center;text-align:center}\n    .hero h1{font-size:clamp(2rem,7vw,4.5rem);font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.03em;margin:0}\n    .row{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 1.2rem}\n    .block{border-radius:18px;padding:2rem;margin:1.2rem 0;color:#fff;font-size:1.4rem;font-weight:700}\n    .b1{background:linear-gradient(120deg,#7c5cff,#a78bff)}.b2{background:linear-gradient(120deg,#2dd4bf,#22a8c0)}\n    .b3{background:linear-gradient(120deg,#ff6ec7,#ff9472)}.b4{background:linear-gradient(120deg,#fbbf24,#f97316)}\n    .hint{position:fixed;bottom:1rem;left:50%;transform:translateX(-50%);color:#5b6377;font-size:.85rem}\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"skewer\" id=\"skewer\">\n    <section class=\"hero\"><h1>Flick to bend ↯</h1></section>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <div class=\"block b1\">Scroll fast and this whole column skews…</div>\n      <div class=\"block b2\">…proportionally to how hard you flick…</div>\n      <div class=\"block b3\">…then springs back to rest when you stop.</div>\n      <div class=\"block b4\">Subtle physics make scrolling feel alive.</div>\n      <div class=\"block b1\">Keep going — try a hard swipe.</div>\n      <div class=\"block b2\">And a slow, gentle one.</div>\n    </div>\n    <section class=\"hero\"><h1>Smooth.</h1></section>\n  </div>\n  <p class=\"hint\">scroll ↑↓</p>\n  <script>\n    var el=document.getElementById('skewer');\n    var max=parseFloat(getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--max-skew'))||8;\n    var reduce=matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;\n    if(!reduce){\n      var last=window.scrollY, cur=0;\n      (function loop(){\n        var now=window.scrollY;\n        var v=now-last; last=now;\n        // smooth toward latest velocity, decay toward 0\n        cur += (v - cur)*0.25; cur *= 0.9;\n        var s=Math.max(-max,Math.min(max, cur*0.4));\n        el.style.transform='skewY('+s+'deg) scaleY('+(1 - Math.abs(s)*0.004)+')';\n        requestAnimationFrame(loop);\n      })();\n    }\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>\n"
}
